                <note rend="inline" type="source">833.34/78: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-17T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 17, 1940—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>100. Your 183, August 16, noon. The Navy Department states that the request of
                    the Uruguayan Government for three destroyers is under consideration but that
                    due to the present strategical situation in the North Atlantic there is small
                    chance for early delivery. The Navy Department states, however, that it is
                    giving the matter further study.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
